<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL ELECTIONS SHERIFF; BLOCK OPPONENT BUYS CABLE TV ADVERTISING IN BID TO 
FORCE RUNOFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Another opponent of Sheriff Sherman Block's bid for reelection to a fourth 
term, Sheriff's Sgt. John R. Stites II, has purchased cable television 
advertising in an attempt to keep Block from amassing a majority of votes in 
Tuesday's election and avoiding a runoff. 
</P>
<P>
 A spokesman for Stites said the purchase totals about $35,000. Earlier in the 
week, it was reported that Block opponent Robert Irmas, a reserve sheriff's 
captain and businessman, had purchased $200,000 in television and radio time, 
including $55,000 on cable. There are six candidates in the race, most of them 
poorly funded political unknowns. 
</P>
