<HEADLINE>
<P>
THANKS FOR KEEPING EVERYBODY IN THE RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As a lifelong baseball fan, I cannot begin to thank major league baseball for 
its decision to create the new six-division format. 
</P>
<P>
 The quality of the game appears to have improved for the simple reason that 
just about every team still has a chance to play in the postseason. 
</P>
<P>
 Though the so-called purists gripe about sub-.500 division leaders, this in 
time will balance itself out. 
</P>
<P>
 And selfishly, as a Dodger fan, I am more than happy to hear what the San 
Francisco Giants are doing. 
</P>
<P>
 MIKE RADLOVIC 
</P>
<P>
 City of Industry 
