<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASEBALL PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CITY SECTION SEMIFINALS 
</P>
<P>
 Chatsworth 5, Taft 0 -- Right-hander Oscar Bocanegra (5-1) hurled a 
four-hitter to lead Chatsworth (28-4) to a victory over Taft (16-16) in a City 
Section 4-A Division semifinal at Pierce College. Top-seeded Chatsworth will 
play El Camino Real for the 4-A championship Monday at Dodger Stadium in a 
rematch of last season's final, won by El Camino Real. 
</P>
<P>
 El Camino Real 6, Kennedy 2 -- Randy Wolf, who was drafted Friday by the 
Dodgers in the 25th round of the major league amateur draft, scattered three 
hits in the final two innings to earn the save for El Camino Real (22-7) in a 
4-A Division semifinal victory over Kennedy (17-11) at Birmingham High. 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Park 2, Lincoln 1 -- Sergio Nolasco hit a double in the top of the 
third inning, advanced to third on a ground out to second by Mario Arambula and 
scored the winning run on an error by third baseman Lico Erami in a Division 
3-A semifinal game at Crystal Springs Park. Huntington Park improved to 12-7. 
Lincoln finished 19-3. 
</P>
<P>
 Franklin 7, South Gate 3 -- Franklin outfielder Roberto Miranda had two hits 
and scored two runs in leading Franklin (20-4-1) to a 3-A Division semifinal 
victory at East LA. 
</P>
