<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION SOFTBALL; CROUCH SHUTS DOWN FOOTHILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BARRY BAUM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The ground around home plate appeared steady, but pitcher Marcy Crouch kept 
Foothill off-balance throughout. The right-handed junior struck out 10 and 
allowed one hit, a single, to lead Huntington Beach Marina to a 2-0 victory in 
the Southern Section Division I softball championship Friday night at Lakewood 
Mayfair Park. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vikings (26-2) finish the season on a 16-game winning streak and allowed 
one run in their five playoff games. 
</P>
<P>
 Heather Hibben's single to left field with two out in the bottom of the fifth 
scored pinch runner Megan Orach from third base for what proved to be the 
winning run. Lynette Velazquez added a sixth-inning RBI double scoring Crouch. 
</P>
<P>
 Crouch (22-2) had 156 strikeouts this season and seven walks Santa Maria St. 
Joseph pitcher Kerri Duncan scattered seven hits and allowed one run to propel 
the Knights (24-6) to a 4-1 victory over La Canada (24-3) in the Division IV 
championship game. BARRY BAUM 
</P>
</TEXT>
