<P>
 GE Jet Engines Focus of Probe: The government is investigating allegations 
that 7,000 military and commercial jet aircraft engines, including the ones 
that power President Clinton's plane, may be defective, the Justice Department 
said. The manufacturer, General Electric Co., denied the allegations, saying 
the engines have flown for more than 200 million hours without an electrical 
problem such as the one in question.The Federal Aviation Administration said it 
