</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Rolls-Royce raced a hand-carried sedan chair through Hong Kong on Friday to 
test traffic congestion.The result: confusion. 
</P>
<P>
 The sedan chair was declared the victor, but the Rolls driver, Ted Thomas, 
claimed he would have won if he had found the finish line. 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas said the race grew out of an argument with fellow businessman Raymond 
Bera about Hong Kong traffic jams. 
</P>
<P>
 Bera reckoned that one could get around the British colony better in chairs 
carried by teams of porters. Thomas said his Rolls could beat anything on 
wheels -- or feet. 
