S. Ross St., and $7 in advance. For more information, call (714) 553-3744. 
</P>
<P>
 Another neighborhood group that recently hosted a separate home tour, the 
Floral Park Neighborhood Assn., on Wednesday awarded $1,800 in proceeds from 
the tour to pay for a college scholarship for Santa Ana High School senior 
Herlinda Guzman.  
</P>
<P>
 That neighborhood group chose Santa Ana High School, Santiago Elementary 
School and a new boxing club called "Turning Kids On" as recipients of home 
tour proceeds, a spokeswoman for that association said. LEE ROMNEY 
