<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; RESIDENTIAL PATROL SERVICES AVAILABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents leaving on vacation this summer can have their homes regularly 
checked by contacting the city Police Services Department. 
</P>
<P>
 The police use the city's senior citizen volunteer group who patrol 
neighborhoods during the summer to make sure homes aren't disturbed while their 
owners are away. 
</P>
<P>
 Uniformed members of the Associated Senior Action Program check ground floor 
windows and doors and immediately report suspicious circumstances to sheriff's 
deputies. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents who want their home looked after must contact the city at least one 
week before the vacation. 
</P>
<P>
 The following information is needed: 
</P>
<P>
 * The dates that patrol services are required, as well as the address and 
cross street of the home. 
</P>
<P>
 * The address and phone number of someone to contact in case of an emergency. 
</P>
<P>
 * A list of when gardeners or cleaners arrive at the home, the name of anyone 
else with access to the home and descriptions of vehicles that will be left in 
the driveway. 
</P>
<P>
 For information about the vacation home security checks, contact the city 
police services department at (714) 443-6369.FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
