WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; PAIR ARRESTED FOR ALLEGED DRUG SALES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Undercover narcotics detectives seized about $20,000 worth of heroin and 
cocaine and arrested two Oxnard residents for allegedly selling drugs at a 
shopping center in Oxnard, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Arturo Fernandez Ochoa, 23, was being held on $50,000 bail at Ventura County 
Jail Friday on suspicion of several drug violations.He is scheduled to be 
arraigned Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 A 17-year-old youth was also arrested and is being held at Juvenile Hall 
pending a court hearing. His identity was withheld because of his age. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said undercover deputies with the Ventura County Sheriff's 
Department and Oxnard police officers arrested the pair about 11:30 a.m. 
Thursday in a shopping center at Pleasant Valley Road and Rose Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Narcotics detectives had purchased drugs from the pair several times in a 
month, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 After investigators arrested the two, they also searched Ochoa's house in the 
4800 block of Olds Road and found cocaine, heroin and $2,800 in cash, 
authorities said. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
