<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIXON LIBRARY EVENTS TO MARK D-DAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Richard Nixon Library & Birthplace will hold two events Monday to mark the 
50th anniversary of D-day. 
</P>
<P>
 The El Toro Memorial Park Committee will hold an anniversary program at the 
library's theater at 11 a.m. The program will include a keynote address by 
Leland Bellot, a history professor at Cal State Fullerton, and music from John 
Huntington. 
</P>
<P>
 Any D-day invasion veterans who are planning to attend the event are asked to 
call (714) 951-9102. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee is comprised of representatives from local chapters of the 
American Legion, Veterans of Foreign Wars, Jewish War Veterans of the USA, 
National Society of the American Revolution and the Orange County Cemetery 
District. 
</P>
<P>
 For admission information, call (714) 951-9102. 
</P>
<P>
 At 7 p.m. Monday, the library will present a forum on foreign policy and world 
trade. The event is sponsored by the National Policy Forum: A Republican Center 
for the Exchange of Ideas. 
</P>
<P>
 U.S. Rep. Christopher Cox (R-Newport Beach) will join former U.S. Ambassador 
to Mexico John Gavin, former U.S. Ambassador to Ireland Peter Dailey and others 
in the discussion with members of the public, who are invited to voice their 
ideas.  
</P>
<P>
 For more information, contact Brett Holmes at (714) 993-5075, Ext. 202. 
</P>
</TEXT>
