<TEXT>
<P>
 Many of this weekend's public affairs shows will either originate from 
Normandy, France, or honor from home the 50th anniversary of the Allied 
invasion. 
</P>
<P>
 Programs commemorating D-day on Sunday include: CNN's "Late Edition's" "From 
Normandy -- 50 Years Later," with President Clinton, who will be aboard the 
U.S.S. George Washington, 2 p.m.; "D-Day: The Total Story," 5 and 9 p.m. Arts & 
Entertainment; and "D-Day: The Great Crusade" highlights "CNN Presents," 6 p.m. 
