USC RECRUIT PLEADS NOT GUILTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 USC football recruit Antione Simpson pleaded not guilty to a sexual assault 
charge Friday in Houston.Arraignment was set for June 29.  
</P>
<P>
 Simpson, 17, and a friend were charged with rape by a 15-year-old girl who 
said the two took turns restraining and assaulting her in her home last Sunday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
 A 6-foot-3, 280-pound defensive end, Simpson signed a letter of intent to 
enroll at USC in January.  
</P>
<P>
 Simpson remained free on $5,000 bond, but his friend, Phillip Gay, 19, 
remained in jail because of a parole violation. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
