<HEADLINE>
<P>
HANAUER LEADS GOLD CUP QUALIFYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAV GLICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The unlimited hydroplane fleet opens its season today on the Detroit River 
with its most prestigious event, the American Power Boat Assn.Gold Cup. 
</P>
<P>
 Chip Hanauer, nine-time Gold Cup champion, was top qualifier in Friday's time 
trials, driving Miss Budweiser on a lap around the egg-shaped 2.5-mile course 
at 162.614 m.p.h. The speed was well below last year's record 170.087 by Mark 
Tate in the Winston Eagle, mainly because of a new fuel restricter valve that 
limits the flow of fuel to the turbine engines. 
</P>
<P>
 Two three-lap heats today and two five-lap heats Sunday will set the field for 
the six-boat Gold Cup championship race later Sunday. Ten boats are expected to 
compete. SHAV GLICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
